---
export const prerender = true;
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About ToolOrbit — Who Built This"
  description="ToolOrbit is built and maintained by a solo developer who wanted fast, ad-light, privacy-respecting tools without the bloat most utility sites ship today."
  canonicalPath="/about"
>
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-2xl px-4 py-16 sm:px-6">
    <h1 class="font-display text-3xl font-bold text-base-50 sm:text-4xl">About ToolOrbit</h1>

    <div class="mt-8 space-y-5 text-base-200 leading-relaxed">
      <p>
        <!-- TODO: replace with your real name + an optional photo before launch.
             Named, real-person authorship is part of Google's E-E-A-T signal
             and AdSense review — "the ToolOrbit team" reads as generic/AI-spun. -->
        Hi, I'm <strong class="text-base-50">Tanvirul Gani Oyon</strong> — I built and maintain ToolOrbit by
        myself, end to end: design, code, content, and the server bill.
      </p>
      <p>
        I kept hitting the same wall as a developer: needing a quick JSON formatter or a UUID
        generator, and landing on a site buried in pop-up ads, fake "download" buttons, and a
        tool that secretly uploads your input to a server you didn't ask about. ToolOrbit exists
        because that shouldn't be the bar.
      </p>
      <p>
        Every tool on this site runs entirely in your browser. There's no backend processing your
        input, no file upload, and no hidden network request — you can check this yourself by
        opening your browser's network tab while using any tool here.
      </p>
      <p>
        ToolOrbit is still early. It started with a focused set of developer tools, built one
        module at a time, with PDF, image, and text tools following as each one is built properly
        rather than rushed out as a thin wrapper around someone else's library.
      </p>
      <p>
        If something's broken, missing, or could be better, the <a
          href="/contact"
          class="text-interactive hover:underline">contact page</a
        > goes straight to me.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
